glosses.gloss: Unnatural lack of color in the skin (as from bruising or sickness or emotional distress)

Pallor is a pale color of the skin that can be caused by illness, emotional shock or stress, stimulant use, or anemia, and is the result of a reduced amount of oxyhaemoglobin and is visible in skin conjuctivae or mucous membrane.
Livor mortis, postmortem lividity, hypostasis or suggillation, is the fourth stage and one of the signs of death.
The congenital absence of pigmentation in the eyes and skin and hair
Albinism in humans is a congenital disorder characterized by the complete or partial absence of pigment in the skin, hair and eyes.
Congenital disorder causing skin to lack pigmentation
A general term for a number of inherited defects of amino acid metabolism in which there is a deficiency or absence of pigment in the eyes, skin, or hair.
Congenital lack of melanin pigmentation in the skin, eyes, and hair or feathers ; the condition of being albino.
